urlText: Opal can be used between Wollongong and Moss Vale, Exeter and Bundanoon stations.
content:
If travelling by Coach between Wollongong station and Moss Vale, Exeter or Bundanoon stations you can use your Opal card or contactless card or device to tap on or off at your origin/destination station provided the origin/destination is an Opal enabled station.

If travelling onto Goulburn, or other Opal enabled station along the Southern Highlands Line, you should not tap off when transferring from Coach to an Intercity train but instead tap off at your destination station.

Booking is not required for Opal customers on this route.
subtitle: Opal can be used between Wollongong and Moss Vale, Exeter and Bundanoon stations.

When using Opal you will need to reserve a seat, at no cost, through the Contact Centre by calling 13 22 32 (Between 07:00 to 22:00 each day).

urlText: Light rail service changes during planned march
content:
Due to a planned march taking place in the Sydney CBD on Sunday 26 January, L1 and L2 light rail services will be temporarily affected between 12pm and 2pm.

Just before the march commences, L2 Randwick Line services will stop running between Circular Quay and Central Chalmers Street and L1 Dulwich Hill Line services will stop running between Convention and Central Grand Concourse. Please change for a nearby Sydney Trains service to continue your trip during this time.

Services will continue to run between Dulwich Hill and Convention and between Randwick and Central in both directions. Light rail services on both lines will resume once the group has safely passed the tracks.
